The paper discusses the performance of deep neural networks on commodity devices, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the performance of DNNs on devices with augmented reality capabilities (cs.AR) and computer vision tasks (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper provides guidelines for designing more efficient DNNs, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and system design (cs.SY).
